  |                                                                         |
  |     Summary                                                             |
  |   -------------------------------------------------------------------   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   In a bizarre universe where the oppressed are on the brink of         |
  |   oblivion, Dandara has awoken to reshape the world.                    |
  |                                                                         |
  |   The world of Salt hangs on the brink of collapse. The citizens,       |
  |   once free spirits, now stand oppressed and isolated. But not all is   |
  |   lost, for out of this aether of fear arises a heroine, a ray of       |
  |   hope. Her name is Dandara.                                            |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Welcome to a unique 2D metroidvania platformer full of mystical       |
  |   creatures and boundless exploration. Defy gravity as you jump         |
  |   across floors, walls, and ceilings alike. Discover the mysteries      |
  |   and secrets hidden throughout the world of Salt and its diverse       |
  |   array of characters. Empower Dandara for combat and survival          |
  |   against enemies bent on oppression.                                   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Awaken, Dandara, to bring freedom and balance to this directionless   |
  |   world.                                                                |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Languages: English, French, Italian, German, Spanish, Portuguese,     |
  |   Russian, Japanese, Korean and Chinese.                                |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Update/Patch Notes: v1.0.4 (v262144).                                 |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Rebalancing of the difficulty curve and general quality updates,    |
  |     examples                                                            |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Shorter time for using essences (Health and Energy flasks)          |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Rebalancing the last boss challenge, for a more fun and fairer      |
  |     one                                                                 |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Rebalancing of the Dream Lands                                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Redesign of the Mosquito enemy                                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Sound alert when Dandara is at low health                           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * New Game+/Challenge options added after finishing the game for      |
  |     the first time. The following can be turned on                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Permadeath, Dandara dies permanently without the ability to         |
  |     respawn                                                             |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Harsh Wounds, Dandara takes double damage                           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * No Grinding, Pleas of Salt can only be found in chests, meaning     |
  |     enemies or destructible objects won't drop them anymore             |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Vengeful Enemies, every enemy spawn a revenge bullet in Dandara's   |
  |     direction when killed. The revenge bullet can be cancelled by       |
  |     leaping through it while it is stationary                           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Easy options added. The following can be enabled                    |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Unlimited Energy, secondary powers won't drain energy               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * After dying, respawn at the last door entered. Enables the player   |
  |     to retry the challenge of each room without the need of             |
  |     backtracking to it                                                  |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * More Flags mode, which adds more checkpoint flags throughout the    |
  |     map                                                                 |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Expanded the Crib of Creation area for better onboarding with the   |
  |     game's mechanics and flow                                           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Tutorial interface updated for mouse and keyboard                   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Vsync toggle added in Main Menu â†’ Options Menu for PC and mobile    |
  |     platforms                                                           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Additional features for veteran Dandara players                     |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * "Hidden" skip cutscene command                                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Keyboard: Ctrl+Shift+(Space Bar - Quick Double Press)               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Controllers: Left Shoulder Button (L1/Z/L/LB) - Quick Double        |
  |     Press                                                               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * Skip new Crib of Creation levels: At The Void, after destroying     |
  |     the first target and opening the door, another target appears       |
  |     floating on the leftmost possible range of that scene. Shoot        |
  |     there to skip the Crib of Creation new tutorial rooms               |
